**Dev PC Terminal 2: Send Stage Commands**
Send these one by one. Wait and inspect after each stage.

1. Drive to approach pose:

```bash
export ROS_DOMAIN_ID=138
source /opt/ros/humble/setup.bash
source ~/gr4_ws/install/setup.bash

ros2 topic pub --once /trolley_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'trolley_ready'}"
```

2. Start left-side ArUco alignment:

```bash
ros2 topic pub --once /trolley_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'side_align'}"
```

3. Drive straight under trolley:

```bash
ros2 topic pub --once /trolley_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'drive_under'}"
```

4. Fine alignment under trolley:

```bash
ros2 topic pub --once /trolley_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'fine_align'}"

ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'mark aruko_node_died'}"


ros2 topic pub --once /trolley_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'trolley_ready'}"
ros2 topic pub --once /trolley_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'side_align'}"

ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'drove_to_far_helped'}"

ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'side_align_stopped_restart'}"

ros2 topic pub --once /trolley_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'check_trolley_type'}"

ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'mark object_detection_correct'}"

ros2 topic pub --once /trolley_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'drive_under'}"
ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'mark drive_under_unsucessfull_retry'}"
ros2 topic pub --once /trolley_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'fine_align'}"

ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'mark fine aling with_light'}"
ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'mark docking sucessfull'}"
ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'mark docking unsucessfull_robot_drove_to_far_under'}"

ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'mark docking sucessfull'}"

ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'mark docking unsucessfull helped'}"

ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'mark docking unsucessfull_retry_with_light'}"

ros2 topic pub --once /trolley_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'deliver_trolley'}"
ros2 topic pub --once /trolley_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'drive_out'}"

ros2 topic pub --once /trolley_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'charging'}"

ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'mark recalibrate_start'}"

ros2 topic pub --once /trolley_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'whole_run_success_with_lights'}"
```

Useful debug commands:

```bash
ros2 topic pub --once /trolley_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'status'}"
ros2 topic pub --once /trolley_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'stop'}"
ros2 topic pub --once /cmd_vel geometry_msgs/msg/Twist "{}"
```

Important: do **not** separately launch `physical_aruco_front_rear.launch.py` while using `physical_staged_trolley_mission.launch.py`, because the staged launch already starts the camera/ArUco nodes it needs.



  
  

